find a: set  of int(1..4)
find b: set  of int(1..4)
find c: set  of int(1..4)
find d: set  of int(1..4)

such that

(sum(flatten([flatten([[ sum([i,j;int(1..2)]) | i <- a, j <- c ],[ sum([i,j;int(1..2)]) | i <- a, j <- d, !(j in c) ];int(1..)]),flatten([[ sum([i,j;int(1..2)]) | i <- b, j <- c, !(i in a) ],[ sum([i,j;int(1..2)]) | i <- b, j <- d, !(i in a), !(j in c) ];int(1..)]);int(1..)])) = 10)

Model before rewriting:

find a: set  of int(1..4)
find b: set  of int(1..4)
find c: set  of int(1..4)
find d: set  of int(1..4)

such that

(sum([ sum([i,j;int(1..2)]) | i <- (a union b), j <- (c union d) ]) = 10)

--

[ sum([i,j;int(1..2)]) | i <- (a union b), j <- (c union d) ], 
   ~~> union_set ([("Base", 8700)])
flatten([[ sum([i,j;int(1..2)]) | i <- a, j <- (c union d) ],[ sum([i,j;int(1..2)]) | i <- b, j <- (c union d), !(i in a) ];int(1..)])

--

[ sum([i,j;int(1..2)]) | i <- a, j <- (c union d) ], 
   ~~> union_set ([("Base", 8700)])
flatten([[ sum([i,j;int(1..2)]) | i <- a, j <- c ],[ sum([i,j;int(1..2)]) | i <- a, j <- d, !(j in c) ];int(1..)])

--

[ sum([i,j;int(1..2)]) | i <- b, j <- (c union d), !(i in a) ], 
   ~~> union_set ([("Base", 8700)])
flatten([[ sum([i,j;int(1..2)]) | i <- b, j <- c, !(i in a) ],[ sum([i,j;int(1..2)]) | i <- b, j <- d, !(i in a), !(j in c) ];int(1..)])

--

Final model:

find a: set  of int(1..4)
find b: set  of int(1..4)
find c: set  of int(1..4)
find d: set  of int(1..4)

such that

(sum(flatten([flatten([[ sum([i,j;int(1..2)]) | i <- a, j <- c ],[ sum([i,j;int(1..2)]) | i <- a, j <- d, !(j in c) ];int(1..)]),flatten([[ sum([i,j;int(1..2)]) | i <- b, j <- c, !(i in a) ],[ sum([i,j;int(1..2)]) | i <- b, j <- d, !(i in a), !(j in c) ];int(1..)]);int(1..)])) = 10)

